Cristiano Ronaldo dos Santos Aveiro (born 5 February 1985) is a Portuguese professional footballer who plays as a forward for Serie A club Juventus and captains the Portugal national team.
Often considered the best player in the world and widely regarded as one of the greatest players of all time,
Ronaldo has won five FIFA Ballon d'or/Best FIFA Men's Player awards, the most for any European player, and four European Golden Shoes.
He has won 29 trophies in his career, including six league titles, five UEFA Champions Leagues, one UEFA European Championship, and one UEFA Nations League.
A prolific goalscorer, Ronaldo holds the record for most goals scored in the UEFA Champions League (127) and the joint record of most goals scored in the UEFA European Championship (9).
He has scored over 700 senior career goals for club and country.